title: Detective.Comics.763-772.Lost.Voices.with.Josie.Mac.FANEDIT.cbr
description:
Detective.Comics.763-772.Lost.Voices.with.Josie.Mac.FANEDIT.cbr

THIS FANEDIT ONLY INCLUDES THE DC BACKUP STORY LOST VOICES FEATURING JOSIE MAC

English CBR (RAR compression)
1 FANEDIT issue 54,229,710bytes 80pages
Source: Detective Comics #763 2001-12 to #772 2002-09

Do you like the DC Comics character Josie Mac? Do you like Gotham Central?

If yes, this 80 page FANEDIT of the Detective Comics backup story Lost Voices should be very enjoyable. Lost Voices spans 10 issues of Detective Comics from #763 2001-12 to #772 2002-09. Lost Voices introduces Josie Mac, a GCPD cop who wants to become a detective. Josie has a psychic superpower which gives her an edge in her job but she has to keep it a secret. Josie appears in 20 of the 40 issues of Gotham Central so Lost Voices is a great read before Gotham Central which starts 5 months after Lost Voices ends.

Note, there is no digital version of Detective Comics 768 Lost Voices Part 6. The digital DC768 only has the main story with no backup story. Multiple scans of DC768 with Lost Voices Part 6 were reviewed and the best version was included with this compilation.
